body: Previous Test Aborted. New Check Test Started: https://jenkins.esgyn.com/job/Check-PR-master/2086/

For hive table and hbase table, cursor103.prepareQuery() will return -1 if there is no related schemas. And for table under seabase, cursor103.prepareQuery returns 0, but cursor103.open() will return -1. It seems we cannot judge if there is on object. So I add the judgment for the existence of SB_HISTOGRAMS table.

+1. Looked at the LOB code related changes and they look fine. The spaces where LOB handle is generated and the LOB descriptor table names are being   derived are the key places. They look fine. A lot of Trace messages used it and they should be fine with sprintf too.

fix to the failure is to update the following line in regress/tools/regress-filter-linux:
  SYSKEY='[0-9]\{17,20\}\>'
(change 18 to 17 as unique ids on some systems return a 17 digit number).
This same issue was seen on another branch.
FYI: I ran this fix through full regressions last night on a clean instance on a workstation. They pass.
